cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the security threat to deep neural networks (DNNs) and proposes a defense mechanism using randomized smoothing. It could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with backdoor attacks and their prevention. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as DNNs are widely used in computer vision tasks. It could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as DNNs are a popular tool in AI research. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with the security of control systems.
